page.title: 11ECOLOGY
page.content:
Toads live in the more remote scrub and marsh.They live underneath rocks and in caves.Unlike frogs and newts there is only one species in this area and the population is not too large either.
Dorset's counryside is abundant with flowers and plants.The hedgrows are alive with flowers of all different colours.Here is a list of some of the flowers in the area. DAISIES BLUEBELLS YELLOW-FLOWERS Common Purple Cowslip Michaelmas White Daffodile Ox-eye Common Honeysuckle Moon Primrose Dandylion Buttercup Celandine
